subsection.p:

\boxed{
    \int_{\partial M}\omega
}

makes sense because
\dim(\partial M)=k-1.


\boxed{
    \int_M d\omega
}

makes sense because d\omega has degree k.

A boundary has no boundary:

\boxed{
    \partial(\partial M)=0.
}

The form version is

\boxed{
    d^2=0.
}

A form is closed if

\boxed{
    d\omega=0.
}

A form is exact if

\boxed{
    \omega=d\eta.
}

Exact implies closed:

\boxed{
    \omega=d\eta
    \quad\Longrightarrow\quad
    d\omega=d^2\eta=0.
}
